    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 20,
        "summary": "Wine is a mocker, and strong drink is raging\u2014Turn to the Lord, and He will save you.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Wine is a mocker, strong drink is raging: and whosoever is deceived thereby is not wise.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Drunkenness; Temperance; Word of Wisdom.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mocking.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The fear of a king is as the roaring of a lion: whoso provoketh him to anger sinneth against his own soul.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:12.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 17:12.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is an honour for a man to cease from strife: but every fool will be meddling.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strife.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ether 12:26.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 62
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0fomenting trouble.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The sluggard will not plow by reason of the cold; therefore shall he beg in harvest, and have nothing.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apathy; Idleness.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0winter; i.e., after the autumn harvest.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Counsel in the heart of man is like deep water; but a man of understanding will draw it out.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 78:2.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 11:26.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 18:4.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Most men will proclaim every one his own goodness: but a faithful man who can find?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The just man walketh in his integrity: his children are blessed after him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Integrity.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A king that sitteth in the throne of judgment scattereth away all evil with his eyes.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 25:5.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Who can say, I have made my heart clean, I am pure from my sin?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 3:23.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 49:8; 109:34.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Divers weights, and divers measures, both of them are alike abomination to the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Even a child is known by his doings, whether his work be pure, and whether it be right.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:16 (16\u201320).",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Work, Value of.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The hearing ear, and the seeing eye, the Lord hath made even both of them.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Love not sleep, lest thou come to poverty; open thine eyes, and thou shalt be satisfied with bread.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Laziness.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is naught, it is naught, saith the buyer: but when he is gone his way, then he boasteth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Boast.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "There is gold, and a multitude of rubies: but the lips of knowledge are a precious jewel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 28:18 (12\u201319).",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Take his garment that is surety for a stranger: and take a pledge of him for a strange woman.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 27:13.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Bread of deceit is sweet to a man; but afterwards his mouth shall be filled with gravel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Food gained by fraudulent means.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Deceit.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Every purpose is established by counsel: and with good advice make war.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 69:4.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 14:31.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 24:6.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that goeth about as a talebearer revealeth secrets: therefore meddle not with him that flattereth with his lips.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Flatter.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso curseth his father or his mother, his lamp shall be put out in obscure darkness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:26; 1\u00a0Ne. 2:11; Mosiah 13:20.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 18:5.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 26:15.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "An inheritance may be gotten hastily at the beginning; but the end thereof shall not be blessed.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Say not thou, I will recompense evil; but wait on the Lord, and he shall save thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forbear; Retribution.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 25:5; 27:14; Isa. 40:31; 2\u00a0Ne. 6:13 (7, 13); D&C 98:2.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Divers weights are an abomination unto the Lord; and a false balance is not good.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0deceptive scales (i.e., made to deceive).",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Man's goings are of the Lord; how can a man then understand his own way?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 10:23.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is a snare to the man who devoureth that which is holy, and after vows to make inquiry.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A wise king scattereth the wicked, and bringeth the wheel over them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kings, Earthly.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The spirit of man is the candle of the Lord, searching all the inward parts of the belly.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Mercy and truth preserve the king: and his throne is upholden by mercy.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The glory of young men is their strength: and the beauty of old men is the gray head.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Beauty.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Old Age.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 19:32; Prov. 16:31.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The blueness of a wound cleanseth away evil: so do stripes the inward parts of the belly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0flogging, strokes, blows.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}